<item>
            <title>[SOLR-3745] SolrCore should fail to init in SolrCloud mode if schema does not contain _version_ field</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-3745</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Basic SolrCloud consistency requires there to be a &lt;tt&gt;&lt;em&gt;version&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/tt&gt; field in the schema.xml, but nothing currently enforces this.  We need a clear and straight forward error in this case so users attempting to upgrade from existing single node Solr setups to multinode SolrCloud setups know they need to modify their configs.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
